Web Client Outdated Notification, New APIs, and BugFixes
This will fix some things up and sorry for not getting this straight away due to being sick :(

Dupe Code
Removed it :)

Background Image Resize Ignored Fix
Width and height is set at 100% and will work on any device now :)

Background image looks better
Now it doesnt look like it was hit by a bus. Beep Beep D:

New Error Pages + OAMPlus Requirement
Error Pages are converted to .js so we dont have to redirect. Saves some time and makes it friendly to reload if Socket server is ever to have temporary downtime.
Plus those who dont claim a client ID will be stuck on install proccess until done. This is to combat a bug back in 2.x spamming the alert.

Error Pages fix for mobile + Mobile warning added + Session is properly checked now :)
Close to 3.0 being finished :D

Song IDs don't change, so back to the old way of random IDs
Since chrome keeps it at 1 ID, we decided to place it back in the function to work properly.

SoundManagers are now in own folder :D
Bye Bye being thrown in OAM-Core.js where its hard to locate.

Fixes + Song Dialog looks better
Nothing like being centered correctly :>

Bugfix for version check duplications + notification sound
Up next. Regions

Fuck IE/Edge Browsers
Since these browsers always have an issue and when we think we fix it, it seems it still has another problem.
TL;DR: No longer supporting IE or Edge browsers. Use Firefox, Chrome, Safari, or Opera

Better unsupportedError.js file
Better said than looking vague.
playlist fix + improvements

OpenAudio App for Windows UWP

Bootstrap Modals are back
Due to an issue with Material's Dialog system, we decided to bring only Bootstrap Modal's back.
Plus this allows us to remove unsupportedError.js as it works with Edge and IE, but philips hue wont work again sadly :(

Volume slider fixed as best as possible for Edge
